<darkcolour>A6416E</darkcolour><section><title>The verb &lt;I&gt;to be&lt;/I&gt;: negative</title><sectiontitle>Make negatives with &lt;I&gt;not&lt;/I&gt;.</sectiontitle><titlesound>ELEMGRAM_1_3_1.mp3</titlesound><text1>I am English</text1><sound1>ELEMGRAM_1_3_2.mp3</sound1><text1a>I am &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;not&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; English</text1a><text2>She is a teacher.</text2><sound2>ELEMGRAM_1_3_3.mp3</sound2><text2a>She is &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;not&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; a teacher.</text2a><titlesound2>ELEMGRAM_1_3_4.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>Listen to the contractions.</sectiontitle2><text3>I am not a student</text3><sound3>ELEMGRAM_1_3_5.mp3</sound3><text3a>I&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;'m not&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; a student.</text3a><text4>He is not American.</text4><sound4>ELEMGRAM_1_3_6.mp3</sound4><text4a>He &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;isn't&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; American.</text4a></section><section><title>The verb &lt;I&gt;to be&lt;/I&gt;: &lt;I&gt;Wh-&lt;/I&gt; questions</title><sectiontitle>Make &lt;I&gt;Wh-&lt;/I&gt; questions with a question word + verb + subject. Use &lt;I&gt;who&lt;/I&gt; for people and &lt;I&gt;what&lt;/I&gt; for things.</sectiontitle><titlesound>ELEMGRAM_1_3_7.mp3</titlesound><text1>your friends</text1><sound1>ELEMGRAM_1_3_8.mp3</sound1><text1a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;Who are&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; your friends?</text1a><text2>it</text2><sound2>ELEMGRAM_1_3_9.mp3</sound2><text2a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;What is&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; it?</text2a><titlesound2>ELEMGRAM_1_3_10.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>Use &lt;I&gt;where&lt;/I&gt; for places and &lt;I&gt;how old&lt;/I&gt; for age.</sectiontitle2><text3>your house</text3><sound3>ELEMGRAM_1_3_11.mp3</sound3><text3a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;Where is &lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;your house?</text3a><text4>your brothers and sisters</text4><sound4>ELEMGRAM_1_3_12.mp3</sound4><text4a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;How old are&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; your brothers and sisters?</text4a></section><section><title>Indefinite article &lt;I&gt;a/an&lt;/I&gt;</title><sectiontitle>Use &lt;I&gt;a/an&lt;/I&gt; for singular nouns.</sectiontitle><titlesound>ELEMGRAM_1_3_13.mp3</titlesound><text1>student</text1><sound1>ELEMGRAM_1_3_14.mp3</sound1><text1a>&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;a&lt;/Font&gt; student</text1a><text2>artist</text2><sound2>ELEMGRAM_1_3_15.mp3</sound2><text2a>&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;an&lt;/Font&gt; artist</text2a><titlesound2>ELEMGRAM_1_3_16.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>Use &lt;I&gt;a&lt;/I&gt; before consonant sounds and &lt;I&gt;an&lt;/I&gt; before vowel sounds.</sectiontitle2><text3>car, doctor, handbag</text3><sound3>ELEMGRAM_1_3_17.mp3</sound3><text3a>&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;a&lt;/Font&gt; car, &lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;a&lt;/Font&gt; doctor, &lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;a&lt;/Font&gt; handbag</text3a><text4>address, uncle, electrician</text4><sound4>ELEMGRAM_1_3_18.mp3</sound4><text4a>&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;an&lt;/Font&gt; address, &lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;an&lt;/Font&gt; uncle, &lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;an&lt;/Font&gt; electrician</text4a></section></grammar>